I'm looking for some advice on how to get rid of this credit card
(from Chase, aptly named).

I cancelled this credit card by phone months ago, with zero balance,
and no recent charges. Everything seemed fine for several months
until one day I get a statement for this card (which I thought was
defunct) showing a balance of about $100. It turns out that (1)
my account had not been closed (it had just been dormant due to
the zero balance), and (2) some shady outfit (Privacy Guard, which
may be connected to, or in cahoots with, Chase), without my
permission, had charged my account for some service I had never
asked for. After hours on phone with both Chase and Privacy Guard
I was told that my account would show a credit for the charges (to
bring it to zero balance), and I it would be closed.

Well, no such luck. Today once again I received a new statement
from Chase showing even more charges (the previous charges plus
late fees). I could, once more, waste a few hours on the phone
clearing this matter, but, after this history, I have no confidence
that it will be resolved this time any more than it did last time.

What are my options other than paying these bogus charges? Is
there some watchdog group I could report Chase to? Will it make
any difference? It has crossed my mind to hire a lawyer, but I
figure that it will cost me more than the bill from Chase. Is
there anything I can tell the Chase customer service flunky on the
other end of the line to convince him/her to stop harassing me?

Thanks!

